page.title: 05PUMPING STATION
page.content: {WINESTEAD PUMPING STATION} Built in 1978 and classed as a Booster Station for a second station situated on the River Humber banks for subsequent discharge from Winestead Drain into the River Humber. It is capable of pumping at a rate of 120 cubic feet per second using 2 electric 140 h.p. pumps. The drainage area covered is 2711 hectares (6700 acres) which is liable to flooding. Included in this area are villages and farms situated in Welwick, Winestead and Patrington. The expected probability of the scheme is 30 years. The Pumping Station is not continuously manned, being capable of remote control operation, but is inspected daily by the Yorkshire Water Authority personnel.
